# Caboodle Site Publishing

## Resource Site Location

All OOUX artifacts are published as markdown files in `site/docs/`.

## Directory Structure

```
site/docs/
├── intro.md                      ← Homepage / getting started
├── process/                      ← ORCA methodology documentation
├── skills/                       ← Skills reference
├── objects/                      ← Object Guides (one .md per object)
│   ├── index.md
│   ├── student.md
│   ├── course.md
│   └── assignment.md
├── projects/                     ← Project-specific ORCA artifacts
│   ├── index.md
│   └── {project-name}/
│       ├── orca-plan.md
│       ├── object-discovery.md
│       ├── nom.md
│       ├── cta-inventory.md
│       ├── attributes.md
│       ├── relationship-lens.md
│       ├── cta-matrix.md
│       ├── shapeshifter-matrix.md
│       ├── object-map.md
│       ├── nav-flow.md
│       ├── cta-prioritization.md
│       ├── object-cards.md
│       ├── user-stories.md
│       ├── relationship-governance.md
│       ├── interaction-specs.md
│       └── data-model.md
├── workshops/                    ← Facilitation materials
└── case-studies/                 ← Completed ORCA examples
```

## Frontmatter Convention

Every published markdown file should include Docusaurus frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: "Object Guide: Student"
sidebar_position: 2
tags: [object-guide, student]
---
```

## File Naming

- Use **kebab-case** for filenames: `object-discovery.md`, `cta-matrix.md`
- Object Guides use the object name: `student.md`, `course.md`
- Project directories use the project name: `projects/my-app/`

## Publishing Rules

1. **Always confirm** with the user before saving a file
2. **Create directories** if they don't exist (use `mkdirSync({ recursive: true })`)
3. **Check for existing files** - if updating, ask the user if they want to overwrite
4. **Include cross-links** to related artifacts in the content
5. **Use relative links** between docs: `[see Object Guide](../objects/student.md)`
6. **Create placeholder pages** for any standard artifact files that don't exist yet (see below)

## Placeholder Pages

**Whenever you publish any artifact to a project directory**, check for and create placeholder pages for all standard artifacts that don't already exist in that directory. This ensures cross-links between artifacts are never broken.

### When to Create Placeholders

- When you first publish ANY artifact to `projects/{project-name}/`
- Check which of the 16 standard files are missing and create stubs for each one

### Standard Project Artifacts (in ORCA order)

| File | sidebar_position | Skill | Prompt |
|------|-----------------|-------|--------|
| `orca-plan.md` | 1 | ORCA Planner | "Plan an ORCA workflow for {project}" |
| `object-discovery.md` | 2 | Object Discovery (01) | "Run the Object Discovery skill for {project}" |
| `nom.md` | 3 | NOM Builder (02) | "Build the NOM for {project}" |
| `cta-inventory.md` | 4 | CTA Inventory (03) | "Run the CTA Inventory skill for {project}" |
| `attributes.md` | 5 | Attribute Definition (04) | "Define attributes for {project}" |
| `relationship-lens.md` | 6 | Relationship Lens (06) | "Run the Relationship Lens skill for {project}" |
| `cta-matrix.md` | 7 | CTA Matrix (07) | "Build the CTA Matrix for {project}" |
| `shapeshifter-matrix.md` | 8 | Shapeshifter Matrix (08) | "Run the Shapeshifter Matrix skill for {project}" |
| `object-map.md` | 9 | Object Map (09) | "Create the Object Map for {project}" |
| `nav-flow.md` | 10 | Nav Flow (10) | "Build the Nav Flow for {project}" |
| `cta-prioritization.md` | 11 | CTA Prioritization (11) | "Prioritize CTAs for {project}" |
| `object-cards.md` | 12 | Object Card (12) | "Design Object Cards for {project}" |
| `user-stories.md` | 13 | OO User Stories (13) | "Write user stories for {project}" |
| `relationship-governance.md` | 14 | Relationship Governance (14) | "Run the Relationship Governance skill for {project}" |
| `interaction-specs.md` | 15 | Interaction Spec (15) | "Write interaction specs for {project}" |
| `data-model.md` | 16 | Data Model Spec (16) | "Build the data model for {project}" |

### Placeholder Template

Use this template for each missing file, substituting the values from the table above:

```markdown
---
title: "{Skill}: {Project Name}"
sidebar_position: {N}
tags: [placeholder]
---

# {Skill}: {Project Name}

> ⏳ **Not yet started.**
>
> Run the **{Skill}** skill to generate this artifact.
>
> Ask your AI assistant: *"{Prompt}"*
```

**Example** - placeholder for `nom.md` in the `renaissance-homepage` project:

```markdown
---
title: "NOM Builder: Renaissance Homepage"
sidebar_position: 3
tags: [placeholder]
---

# NOM Builder: Renaissance Homepage

> ⏳ **Not yet started.**
>
> Run the **NOM Builder (02)** skill to generate this artifact.
>
> Ask your AI assistant: *"Build the NOM for renaissance-homepage"*
```

## After Publishing

After saving an artifact (and its placeholders), always:
1. Confirm the file path to the user
2. Suggest the next skill in the workflow
3. Mention they can preview with `cd site && npm install && npm start`
